{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"728bf184"},"source":["# Dementia Classification using Triplet Network and MobileNetV2\n","\n","This notebook demonstrates a deep learning approach for classifying dementia from medical images, specifically distinguishing between 'Non_Demented' and 'Very_Mild_Dementia' cases. The methodology leverages a Triplet Network architecture with a MobileNetV2 backbone for feature extraction, combined with a custom hybrid distance metric and triplet loss function.\n","\n","## Table of Contents\n","\n","1.  **Setup and Data Loading:** Initializes the environment and loads preprocessed image data from Google Drive.\n","2.  **Data Preprocessing and Augmentation:** Performs sanity checks on the data and applies augmentation techniques to increase dataset diversity.\n","3.  **Triplet Sampling, Distance, and Loss Definition:** Defines the core components of the Triplet Network, including a custom triplet generation function, a hybrid distance metric (Euclidean, Cosine, EMD), and the triplet loss function.\n","4.  **Model Architecture (Triplet Network):** Constructs the Triplet Network using MobileNetV2 as the base encoder, followed by L2 normalization of embeddings.\n","5.  **Model Compilation and Training:** Compiles the Triplet Network with a custom optimizer and trains it using the generated triplet data.\n","6.  **Embedding Extraction and Classifier Training:** Extracts embeddings from the trained Triplet Network and uses them to train a separate dense classifier for the binary classification task.\n","7.  **Model Evaluation and Visualization:** Evaluates the performance of the classifier and visualizes training history, including loss, accuracy, and memory usage."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["###Start\n"],"metadata":{"id":"ecs4dW06ANT6"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"4c41ca2f"},"source":["## Setup and Data Loading\n","\n","This section handles the initial setup of the Colab environment, including mounting Google Drive to access stored data and importing necessary libraries. It then loads the preprocessed training and testing image datasets along with their corresponding labels."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["This version is the most normal version of all versions. In this version unitary initialization used but BN and L2 have been removed from architecture of the model.\n"],"metadata":{"id":"yMxdDHx3ANT8"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"203464b7"},"source":["This cell imports all necessary libraries for the project, including TensorFlow for building and training neural networks, NumPy for numerical operations, Matplotlib for plotting, Keras layers for model construction, ImageDataGenerator for data augmentation, and scikit-learn for evaluation metrics."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"XFO08h7iANT9"},"outputs":[],"source":["import tensorflow as tf\n","import numpy as np\n","import os, random\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","from keras import layers\n","from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator\n","from tensorflow.keras import regularizers\n","from tensorflow.keras.callbacks import ModelCheckpoint\n","from tensorflow.keras.models import load_model\n","from tensorflow.keras.optimizers.schedules import ExponentialDecay\n","from tensorflow.keras.optimizers import Adam\n","from imblearn.over_sampling import RandomOverSampler\n","from sklearn.metrics import classification_report\n","import time\n","import psutil"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"5c70f7f8"},"source":["To access the dataset stored in Google Drive, the notebook needs to mount Google Drive to the Colab environment. This allows file operations directly from the notebook."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1720189270798,"user_tz":-210,"elapsed":19832,"user":{"displayName":"Atta Maleki","userId":"02166432465120845957"}},"outputId":"8ce0a8d9-0b2e-41d8-8c44-cc8b736ed4f1","id":"4_mxOSkZANT-"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Mounted at /content/drive\n"]}],"source":["from google.colab import drive\n","drive.mount('/content/drive')"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"24a72800"},"source":["The preprocessed training and testing image datasets, along with their corresponding labels, are loaded from the specified path in Google Drive. These are NumPy arrays containing image data and one-hot encoded labels."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"1TQWoGCHANT-"},"outputs":[],"source":["path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/OASIS_P/pre/'\n","trainImages = np.load(path + 'trainImages.npy')\n","trainLabels = np.load(path + 'trainLabels.npy')\n","testImages  = np.load(path + 'testImages.npy')\n","testLabels  = np.load(path + 'testLabels.npy')"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"3899df2c"},"source":["A sanity check is performed on the loaded image data to ensure there are no NaN (Not a Number) or Inf (Infinity) values, which could cause issues during model training."]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Sanity check for data\n","print(\"Checking data for NaN or Inf values...\")\n","assert not np.any(np.isnan(trainImages)), \"trainImages contains NaN values\"\n","assert not np.any(np.isinf(trainImages)), \"trainImages contains Inf values\"\n","assert not np.any(np.isnan(testImages)), \"testImages contains NaN values\"\n","assert not np.any(np.isinf(testImages)), \"testImages contains Inf values\"\n","print(\"Data checks passed.\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"X3eTo0S8Rp1F","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1720189303837,"user_tz":-210,"elapsed":1408,"user":{"displayName":"Atta Maleki","userId":"02166432465120845957"}},"outputId":"ce9dfdd6-dbc8-41e0-f022-b559228cd6e0"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Checking data for NaN or Inf values...\n","Data checks passed.\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"11a6e616"},"source":["Data augmentation is applied to both the training and test datasets using `ImageDataGenerator`. This technique helps to increase the diversity of the training data and prevent overfitting by applying random transformations like rotation, shifts, and flips. Two separate generators are used, one for more aggressive augmentation on training data and a milder one for test data (though often test data is not augmented)."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"Me2MuFl0ANUC"},"source":["###Data Check"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"NsdAyzuIANUB"},"outputs":[],"source":["augmented = ImageDataGenerator(rotation_range=7,\n","                               width_shift_range = 0.01,\n","                               height_shift_range= 0.01,\n","                               zoom_range=0.1,\n","                               horizontal_flip= True)\n","augmented.fit(trainImages)\n","#augmented.fit(testImages)"]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["augmented2 = ImageDataGenerator(rotation_range=1,\n","                               width_shift_range = 0.0001,\n","                               height_shift_range= 0.0001,\n","                               zoom_range=0.001,\n","                               horizontal_flip= True)\n","augmented2.fit(testImages)"],"metadata":{"id":"NV5J3Lrxsu16"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"8f9127f4"},"source":["Before proceeding with model training, it's good practice to visualize a sample of the loaded images and check their shapes and data types to ensure correct loading and preprocessing."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"elapsed":856,"status":"ok","timestamp":1720164528664,"user":{"displayName":"Atta Maleki","userId":"09673812612104214910"},"user_tz":-210},"outputId":"1e5dc32b-cddf-4a0d-bcd9-44876158afc2","id":"X733B8ZPANUC"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["(53780, 64, 64, 3)   float32\n","(53780, 2)\n","(13444, 64, 64, 3)\n","(13444, 2)\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"source":["#Data Loading Check\n","plt.imshow(trainImages[254])\n","print(trainImages.shape, \" \", trainImages.dtype)\n","print(trainLabels.shape)\n","print(testImages.shape)\n","print(testLabels.shape)"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"elapsed":1388,"status":"ok","timestamp":1720164532138,"user":{"displayName":"Atta Maleki","userId":"09673812612104214910"},"user_tz":-210},"outputId":"7d5c675f-2d8d-4971-e1a7-7dc56d283cfa","id":"q6aVA7JVANUD"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1200x1200 with 20 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"source":["\\\n","classes = ['Non_Demented', 'Very_Mild_Dementia']\n","\n","figure, axes = plt.subplots(4, 5, figsize= (12,12))\n","for i in range(len(trainImages)):\n","  if trainLabels[i][0] == 1 :\n","    titleIndex = 0\n","  else :\n","    titleIndex = 1\n","  ax_row = i // 5\n","  ax_col = i % 5\n","  if ax_row ==4 or ax_col==5:\n","    break\n","  ax = axes[ax_row][ax_col]\n","  ax.imshow(trainImages[i])\n","  ax.set_title(classes[titleIndex])\n","  ax.axis('off')\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"7303287b"},"source":["This section defines the core components of the Triplet Network: a function to generate triplets (anchor, positive, negative image pairs), a custom hybrid distance metric, and the triplet loss function. The triplet loss aims to ensure that the distance between an anchor and a positive sample is smaller than the distance between the anchor and a negative sample by a certain margin (`alpha`)."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["###Triplet sampling and distance and Loss def\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"kZflLGcsuOHm"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["\n","# Triplet sampling function\n","def generate_triplets(images, labels, num_triplets):\n","    triplets = []\n","    class_indices = {0: np.where(labels == 0)[0], 1: np.where(labels == 1)[0]}  # Assuming classes are 0 and 1\n","\n","    for _ in range(num_triplets):\n","        anchor_class = np.random.choice([0, 1])\n","        negative_class = 1 - anchor_class  # The opposite class\n","\n","        anchor_idx = np.random.choice(class_indices[anchor_class])\n","        positive_idx = np.random.choice(class_indices[anchor_class])\n","        negative_idx = np.random.choice(class_indices[negative_class])\n","\n","        anchor_image = images[anchor_idx]\n","        positive_image = images[positive_idx]\n","        negative_image = images[negative_idx]\n","\n","        triplets.append((anchor_image, positive_image, negative_image))\n","\n","    return triplets\n"],"metadata":{"id":"e0L9n2rMuKx1"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Custom hybrid distance and triplet loss function\n","def hybrid_distance(a, b, w1=0.33, w2=0.33, w3=0.34):\n","    euclidean_dist = tf.reduce_sum(tf.square(a - b), axis=-1)\n","    cosine_sim = tf.reduce_sum(a * b, axis=-1) / (tf.sqrt(tf.reduce_sum(tf.square(a), axis=-1)) * tf.sqrt(tf.reduce_sum(tf.square(b), axis=-1)))\n","    cosine_sim = tf.clip_by_value(cosine_sim, -1.0, 1.0)  # Ensure cosine similarity is within valid range\n","    emd_dist = tf.abs(tf.cumsum(a, axis=-1) - tf.cumsum(b, axis=-1))\n","\n","    return w1 * euclidean_dist + w2 * (1 - cosine_sim) + w3 * tf.reduce_sum(emd_dist, axis=-1)\n","\n","@tf.function\n","def triplet_loss(y_true, y_pred, alpha=0.2, w1=0.33, w2=0.33, w3=0.34):\n","    anchor, positive, negative = tf.split(y_pred, num_or_size_splits=3, axis=1)\n","    pos_dist = hybrid_distance(anchor, positive, w1, w2, w3)\n","    neg_dist = hybrid_distance(anchor, negative, w1, w2, w3)\n","\n","    # Debug prints to check intermediate values\n","    # tf.print(\"Anchor:\", anchor, summarize=10)\n","    # tf.print(\"Positive:\", positive, summarize=10)\n","    # tf.print(\"Negative:\", negative, summarize=10)\n","    # tf.print(\"Pos Dist:\", pos_dist, summarize=10)\n","    # tf.print(\"Neg Dist:\", neg_dist, summarize=10)\n","\n","    loss = tf.maximum(pos_dist - neg_dist + alpha, 0.0)\n","    return tf.reduce_mean(loss)"],"metadata":{"id":"krg8oMjcwJyW"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"8b18711e"},"source":["Here, the Triplet Network architecture is constructed. It uses a pre-trained MobileNetV2 as the base encoder to extract features from the input images. The embeddings generated by MobileNetV2 are then L2 normalized to ensure they lie on a unit hypersphere, which is beneficial for distance-based metrics."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"Vk9QuDr1ANUG"},"source":["###MODEL"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"D4IEb5xPANUH","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1720189309901,"user_tz":-210,"elapsed":4623,"user":{"displayName":"Atta Maleki","userId":"02166432465120845957"}},"outputId":"989a9532-f9b1-414b-a8f1-0d9b0e655077"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stderr","text":["WARNING:tensorflow:`input_shape` is undefined or non-square, or `rows` is not in [96, 128, 160, 192, 224]. Weights for input shape (224, 224) will be loaded as the default.\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Downloading data from https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/keras-applications/mobilenet_v2/mobilenet_v2_weights_tf_dim_ordering_tf_kernels_1.0_224_no_top.h5\n","9406464/9406464 [==============================] - 0s 0us/step\n"]}],"source":["\n","# Triplet network\n","def create_base_network(input_shape):\n","    base_model = tf.keras.applications.MobileNetV2(input_shape=input_shape, include_top=False, pooling='avg')\n","    return base_model\n","\n","input_shape = (64, 64, 3)\n","base_network = create_base_network(input_shape)\n","\n","anchor_input = tf.keras.layers.Input(input_shape, name='anchor_input')\n","positive_input = tf.keras.layers.Input(input_shape, name='positive_input')\n","negative_input = tf.keras.layers.Input(input_shape, name='negative_input')\n","\n","anchor_embedding = base_network(anchor_input)\n","positive_embedding = base_network(positive_input)\n","negative_embedding = base_network(negative_input)\n","\n","# Normalize embeddings\n","anchor_embedding = tf.keras.layers.Lambda(lambda x: tf.math.l2_normalize(x, axis=1))(anchor_embedding)\n","positive_embedding = tf.keras.layers.Lambda(lambda x: tf.math.l2_normalize(x, axis=1))(positive_embedding)\n","negative_embedding = tf.keras.layers.Lambda(lambda x: tf.math.l2_normalize(x, axis=1))(negative_embedding)\n","\n","merged_output = tf.keras.layers.Concatenate(axis=1)([anchor_embedding, positive_embedding, negative_embedding])\n","\n","triplet_model = tf.keras.models.Model(inputs=[anchor_input, positive_input, negative_input],\n","                      outputs=merged_output)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"893d9512"},"source":["The Triplet Network model is compiled using the Adam optimizer and the custom `triplet_loss` function defined earlier. This prepares the model for the feature embedding learning phase."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["###Model compile###"],"metadata":{"id":"PWjEqv95ANUM"}},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"ELKUdYADANUN"},"outputs":[],"source":["optimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.00001, clipnorm=1.0)\n","triplet_model.compile(optimizer=optimizer, loss=triplet_loss)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"cb73cdb0"},"source":["A custom data generator `TripletDataGenerator` is implemented to efficiently generate batches of triplets (anchor, positive, negative) during the training of the Triplet Network. This ensures that the model is continuously fed with relevant triplet examples."]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Custom data generator\n","class TripletDataGenerator(tf.keras.utils.Sequence):\n","    def __init__(self, images, labels, batch_size=32, num_triplets=25000):\n","        self.images = images\n","        self.labels = labels\n","        self.batch_size = batch_size\n","        self.num_triplets = num_triplets\n","        self.triplets = self._generate_triplets()\n","\n","    def _generate_triplets(self):\n","        return generate_triplets(self.images, self.labels, self.num_triplets)\n","\n","    def __len__(self):\n","        return int(np.ceil(len(self.triplets) / self.batch_size))\n","\n","    def __getitem__(self, idx):\n","        batch_triplets = self.triplets[idx * self.batch_size:(idx + 1) * self.batch_size]\n","        anchor_images = np.array([t[0] for t in batch_triplets])\n","        positive_images = np.array([t[1] for t in batch_triplets])\n","        negative_images = np.array([t[2] for t in batch_triplets])\n","        return [anchor_images, positive_images, negative_images], np.zeros((len(anchor_images),))  # Adjusting the shape\n","\n","train_generator = TripletDataGenerator(trainImages, trainLabels, batch_size=32)\n","test_generator = TripletDataGenerator(testImages, testLabels, batch_size=32)\n"],"metadata":{"id":"7Z344kWpxxAG"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"ecf21b2a"},"source":["These cells provide a visual representation (`plot_model`) and a summary (`summary()`) of the Triplet Network's architecture, showing its layers, output shapes, and the number of parameters. This helps in understanding the model's structure."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"2qk27MuKANUP"},"source":["###Model Check"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":276},"executionInfo":{"elapsed":1111,"status"